      "honest_assessment": "Simple statistical baselines (KL, chi-squared, frequency) can detect behavioral divergence between configurations comparably to the coalgebraic pipeline for per-prompt divergence detection. The coalgebraic pipeline's value lies in: (1) reusable automaton model checked against multiple temporal specs without re-querying, (2) graded satisfaction degrees in [0,1], (3) Kantorovich bisimulation distance for version comparison, (4) counterexample witnesses, and (5) multi-step temporal property verification (e.g., refusal persistence). For single-property divergence detection alone, a chi-squared test is sufficient and cheaper."
